# ACCESS-XR

Official implementation of **ACCESS-XR: A Unified Multimodal System for Inclusive and Accessible Communication in Extended Reality**.

---

## Overview

ACCESS-XR is a unified multimodal communication framework designed to improve accessibility and inclusivity in Extended Reality (XR) environments. The framework integrates gesture recognition, speech understanding, semantic translation, and uncertainty-aware decision-level fusion to enable seamless interaction among users with diverse communication abilities.

The system combines computer vision, automatic speech recognition, semantic reasoning, and real-time XR rendering within a modular architecture suitable for edge and cloud deployment.

---

## Key Features

- Lightweight attention-enhanced YOLOv8 gesture recognition
- Whisper-based automatic speech recognition with entropy-aware confidence estimation
- Fuzzy semantic mapping for multimodal translation
- Uncertainty-aware decision-level fusion
- Real-time multimodal communication
- FastAPI backend
- React Native frontend
- Edge/cloud deployment support
- Modular architecture for future multimodal foundation models

